The paper deals with algorithms for multidimensional data processing, which is a topic that falls under several sub-categories of computer science. The focus on clustering and diameter computation suggests that cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.DB (Databases) are likely sub-categories. The use of a new distance function and string processing problems suggest cs.CG (Computational Geometry) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as possible sub-categories. Finally, the theoretical analysis and experimental evaluation suggest cs.LG (Machine Learning) as a potential sub-category.
